{"name":"Monastic Code","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Monastic Code</p>\n<p>You are a student on the path to enlightenment, a scholar of the way.</p>\n<p>Choose what you believe i s the key to right action. The first time each session you o ffer someone advice pertaining to your code, that person takes +1 forward to follow your advice, and i f they act on i t, you both mark 1 XP.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Relinquishment of all material attachments</li>\n<li>Strict adherence to rigorous ethics</li>\n<li>Discovery and openness to experience</li>\n<li>Complete mastery of your martial art</li>\n<li>Creation of and participation i n a more perfect society ❏Unceasing critical examination of philosophic texts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2e1LE9AlxyzPyP7H"}
{"name":"Student Of The Four Ways","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Student Of The Four Ways</p>\n<p>Choose one element that you can shape (earth, wind, water, or fire).</p>\n<p>When you b end that element to your will, roll+WIS.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, i t does as you command, taking the shape and movement you desire for a time.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9 the effect i s short-lived and weak, l asting only a moment.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"WIS","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5wODplxaIUiIhqp0"}
{"_id":"7uzVjRLvZ8OFDfoH","name":"The Monk","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Monk</h2>\n<p>Look, it&rsquo;s not all, &ldquo;wuxia dragon punch&rdquo; and &ldquo;ninja-style jutsu&rdquo;, okay?</p>\n<p>Sure, sometimes you&rsquo;ve been known to leap up and then climb a sheer cliff wall. There was that time when you did divert that kobold&rsquo;s spear with one-hand and knocked him and all his buddies in the river. And everyone remembers how you punched directly through the archduke&rsquo;s chest when you found out he was responsible for slaughtering countless innocent lives. That&rsquo;s not what it means to be you. You&rsquo;re so much more.</p>\n<p>They don&rsquo;t see that moment of quiet contemplation. They don&rsquo;t</p>\n<p>see the years of study, of practice, of failing. They don&rsquo;t see that it&rsquo;s the truth that lights your path, that draws your breath, that moves your hand.</p>\n<p>They will. You can show them. Stay true, Monk.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Names</h2>\n<p>Name: Xuanzang, Vardha, Benedict, Akeha, Junfan, Theresa, Sun Li, Korra, Tenzin, Jackie</p>\n<p>Moniker: The Pilgrim, The Fist, The Wise, The Mad, The Skillful, The Peaceful, The Silent</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<p>EYES: Piercing, Wandering, Calm, or _ ___________</p>\n<p>BODY: Thin, Tense, Muscular, or _ ___________</p>\n<p>ROBES: Plain, Heavy, Colorful, or _ ___________</p>\n<p>HANDS: Clean, Calloused, Wrinkled, or _ ___________</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bonds</h2>\n<p>I respect ___________&rsquo;s ways and beliefs, but they are seriously misguided. They must be shown the truth.</p>\n<p>______________ i s brash and foolish - I must teach them patience and wisdom.</p>\n<p>_____________ i s also on the true path, and I appreciate their insight.</p>\n<p>I fear ___________&rsquo;s strength, and they will fear mine.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<p>You try to travel l ight:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A Token of your monastery or your travels, describe it: ___________________________________________________________________________</li>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, ration, 1 weight), Uses l eft: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n<li>Adventuring Gear (5 uses, 1 weight), Uses left: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n<li>1 coin</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose a weapon, i f you want one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sword ( close, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Staff ( close, t wo-handed, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Sickle ( hand, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Spear ( reach, thrown, near, 1 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>The Monk Moves</h2>\n<p>● Martial Art</p>\n<p>○ In a sense, this is a more specific Defy Danger move with the option of dealing damage on a success, but to trigger it, the Monk must explain how they use the attack as an opening - it doesn&rsquo;t automatically trigger whenever the Monk is about to take damage, especially at ranges outside the Monk&rsquo;s reach.</p>\n<p>○ This move also likely adds complications to Hack &amp; Slash - if the Monk is about to take an enemy&rsquo;s attack (as per the 7-9 text of Hack &amp; Slash), can the Monk interject to trigger Martial Art? The answer will be dependent on the fiction, but often I don&rsquo;t think that Defy Danger could trigger under these circumstances either - the attack happening is often part of the resolution of Hack &amp; Slash. Put another way, by choosing to Hack &amp; Slash, a Monk is typically not using an enemy&rsquo;s attack against them, but instead acting on the offensive.</p>\n<p>● Lethal Weapon</p>\n<p>○ Notice that this does not make the Monk&rsquo;s body a weapon for Hack &amp; Slash purposes - it is up to the GM if an unarmed monk can trigger Hack &amp; Slash in the moment.</p>\n<p>● The Way of Steel</p>\n<p>○ Conversely to Lethal Weapon, using Martial Art can make your weapon more effective for Hack &amp; Slash.</p>\n<p>● Closed Fist and Open Palm</p>\n<p>○ Once you have taken one of these moves, you can not take the other.</p>\n<p>● Return Fire</p>\n<p>○ Just as Martial Art doesn&rsquo;t automatically trigger when the Monk defies the danger of a melee attack, so too for Return Fire. In order to deal damage with Return Fire, the Monk must be able to throw or shoot the ranged shot back.</p>\n<p>● Deeply Spiritual</p>\n<p>○ This move allows the Monk to talk to animals from their native land, and also gives a specific condition (spend time in meditative contemplation) to learn how to speak to additional animals.</p>\n<p>● Nature&rsquo;s Pupil</p>\n<p>○ This opens up animal moves, such as the Druid has access to when Shapeshifted (e.g.</p>\n<p>trample them, escape to the air, drag them to the ground, etc).</p>\n<p>● Journey to the West</p>\n<p>○ Although a possible outcome is that the traveler you meet on the way would want to become your hireling, it is not guaranteed.</p>\n<p>● Revolutionary Praxis</p>\n<p>○ Debate is a common, but certainly not the exclusive, way to test philosophies.</p>\n<p>● One With Nothing</p>\n<p>○ Like other moves that use bonds as resources, the intention here is that there is some maximum number of bonds (set by the GM and player) and that erasing that bond for the purpose of this move indicates that you have one fewer bond for the rest of time. Erasing a bond for this move might also imply a serious change in the Monk&rsquo;s relationship with a person, although players are free to interpret this how they wish.</p>","races":{"0":{"label":"Disciple","description":"You’re a l earned student of philosophy, having spent most of your l ife i n a monastery. When e thics, truth, or beauty is your leverage, you may Parley using WIS i nstead of CHA."},"1":{"label":"Hermit","description":"You’re a wanderer, a distant traveler who has spent most of your life i n solitary contemplation. When you spend time in quiet meditation, the GM will tell you something pertinent to your current situation or l ocation, or tell you that you already know everything there i s to know. They might ask you how your meditation revealed this to you."},"2":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Neutral","description":"Resolve conflict peacefully."},"1":{"label":"Lawful","description":"Follow your monastic code without compromise."},"2":{"label":"Good","description":"Endanger yourself or give something up to help those in need."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"","mode":"checkbox","items":["6JcOoZ8CNqYxLgyQ","YwHV7WYzTPSAOorl","2BeMe3ztQ8QlEAYp"]},"1":{"label":"","mode":"radio","items":["Bj8EezgO0DZ9OhVQ","xu45M9oglN3VEWHC","4wGxPYN283j74dcF","VexRYKlHs8z9OIbK"]}},"hp":6,"load":6,"damage":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
