{"_id":"i1JO1X0Dowxy9QEH","name":"Like Flowing Water","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Like Flowing Water</p>\n<p>When you r edirect an enemy&rsquo;s melee attack to another closeby creature, roll+DEX.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, the attack i s fully redirected, and a target of your choice takes the attacker&rsquo;s damage.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, both you and your target take damage.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"DEX","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GwwwXyIQbkQrGSyd","name":"Like Solid Iron","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Like Solid Iron</p>\n<p>When you s trike a powerful stance and Defend, you can roll+WIS instead of CON.</p>\n<p>For as long as you have hold this way, you can&rsquo;t be moved and you have +2 armor.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"WIS","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"D02JENK2bbiHaAHm","name":"Martial Art","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you use an opponent&rsquo;s melee attack against them , roll+DEX.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you accurately and deftly deflect the attack. You can choose to take no damage, or to deal your damage and take their damage-1d6.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<p>● You dodge the attack, but l ose your position or footing.</p>\n<p>● You and your opponent each deal your damage -1d4</p>\n<p>● You take the enemy&rsquo;s attack but bring them out of position or into danger, take +1 forward against them</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"DEX","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FRwXLnjLzvs4QqzP","name":"Meteor Punch","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Meteor Punch</p>\n<p>When you strike with forbidden force, roll+STR. Your blow creates shockwaves, rends earth and sky, and destroys buildings. Everyone and everything i n the area takes damage as appropriate.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, your application of this dangerous technique i s flawless.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, the effect is out of control, and collateral damage i s i ntense.</p>\n<p>On a 6-, no mortal body was meant to wield such power.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"STR","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2e1LE9AlxyzPyP7H","name":"Monastic Code","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Monastic Code</p>\n<p>You are a student on the path to enlightenment, a scholar of the way.</p>\n<p>Choose what you believe i s the key to right action. The first time each session you o ffer someone advice pertaining to your code, that person takes +1 forward to follow your advice, and i f they act on i t, you both mark 1 XP.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Relinquishment of all material attachments</li>\n<li>Strict adherence to rigorous ethics</li>\n<li>Discovery and openness to experience</li>\n<li>Complete mastery of your martial art</li>\n<li>Creation of and participation i n a more perfect society ❏Unceasing critical examination of philosophic texts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xfMr9TBEFHV8Hzls","name":"Nature’s Pupil","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Nature&rsquo;s Pupil</p>\n<p>Requires Deeply Spiritual</p>\n<p>When you <strong>combine your Martial Art with the lessons of an animal spirit you&rsquo;ve studied</strong>, on a hit you can make a move of an animal whose spirit you&rsquo;ve studied (instead of any other option).</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Deeply Spiritual","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jaE9Cu6ufFJvjC37","name":"On The Move","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>On The Move</p>\n<p>When you d efy a danger caused by movement (maybe falling off a narrow bridge or gracefully dancing past an armed guard) take +1.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Yik6NaSwMIzTcqkS","name":"One With Nothing","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>One With Nothing</p>\n<p>When you empty your mind and embrace the end of the self, erase one bond permanently and hold 3 emptiness.</p>\n<p>Spend 1 emptiness to describe your perfect reaction to danger and defy it as though you had rolled a 10+.</p>\n<p>When you have no bonds and no emptiness, you become a GM character.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"s5yNm6hPgsJai9hG","name":"Open Palm","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Open Palm</p>\n<p>Mutually exclusive with Closed Fist While you refuse to retaliate with violence in accordance with your monastic code, you take +1 ongoing to Parley, Defend, and Aid/Interfere.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"cYlANk0Q1lGU2PZD","name":"Padawan","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Padawan</p>\n<p>When you Recruit, on a hit you&rsquo;ll always find someone who wants to be your student and whose cost is in line with your Monastic Code.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FrJzzYqn5La2lFgy","name":"Perfect Technique","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Perfect Technique</p>\n<p>When you w ield your Martial Art and roll a 12+ you find your enemy&rsquo;s weakness and strike true.</p>\n<p>You avoid their attack and can choose to deal your damage or temporarily stun them, rendering them helpless.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"CRQQK4hDqTz7mkrd","name":"Return Fire","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Return Fire</p>\n<p>You can deflect ranged attacks with your Martial Art.</p>\n<p>You can still choose to deal your damage when you deflect ranged attacks.</p>\n<p>Ammo and other ranged shots you wield gain the thrown, near tags.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mOnUzGGxN0XWyC5a","name":"Revolutionary Praxis","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Revolutionary Praxis</p>\n<p>When you prove the superiority of your philosophy to someone in power, take +1 ongoing with or against their followers while they believe in you.</p>","class":"The Monk","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
